22    /**
23    * The class RandomVariableFromFloatArray represents a random variable being the evaluation of a stochastic process
24    * at a certain time within a Monte-Carlo simulation.
25    * It is thus essentially a vector of floating point numbers - the realizations - together with a double - the time.
26    * The index of the vector represents path.
27    * The class may also be used for non-stochastic quantities which may potentially be stochastic
28    * (e.g. volatility). If only non-stochastic random variables are involved in an operation the class uses
29    * optimized code.
30    *
31    * Accesses performed exclusively through the interface
32    * <code>RandomVariable</code> is thread safe (and does not mutate the class).
33    *
34    * This implementation uses floats for the realizations (consuming less memory compared to using doubles). However,
35    * the calculation of the average is performed using double precision.
36    *
37    * @author Christian Fries
38    * @version 1.8
39    */
 
36.6% Uncovered Elements: 677 (1,067) Complexity: 300 Complexity Density: 0.49
